result.execSummary:
The defendant Andrew L. White was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Identity Theft - Financial Gain [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).
  • Identity Theft - Financial Gain [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
1:32 pm cases 22CF111, 22CF153, 22CF214 called. Defendant Andrew L. White appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Zebulon Patek in court for Andrew L. White.  Prosecuting attorney Andrew Gunderson in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defense recited the joint agreement. Defendant waives their right to appear in person and Court accepts waiver. State in compliance with victim notification requirements. 
Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. Defendant acknowledges prior convictions to support repeater enhancer. 
In 22CF153: Defendant pleads Guilty to Count 1 of the Information. 
In 22CF214: Defendant pleads Guilty to Counts 1 and 2 of the Information. 
In 22CF111: Defendant pleads Guilty to Count 4 of the Information. 
Court accepts pleas and finds the defendant Guilty. Anything else is dismissed and read in. 
Parties ask the Court to follow the joint agreement. Defendant makes a statement before sentencing. 

As to 22CF153: Defendant is sentenced to 4 years initial confinement and 3 years extended supervision. 
As to 22CF111 and 22CF214: Defendant is sentenced to 3 years initial confinement and 2 years extended supervision on each count. 
All sentences run concurrent to one another and any other sentence currently being served. 

Conditions of extended supervision include: 
Complete AODA and follow through with recommendations. Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge. 
Maintain absolute sobriety. Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. 
No Contact with D.M., Walmart, The Buckle or Scheels. 
No contact with any known drug dealers/users except in a therapeutic setting. 
Defendant to pay restitution in the amount of $69.15 (includes surcharge) to 
Defendant to pay court costs including applicable surcharges and $120 in WCDTF buy funds. 
Defendant is eligible for CIP and SAP. 
Defendant has 0 days credit in 22CF153, 3 days credit in 22CF214 and 2 days credit in 22CF111.
